stylometry: First, the safety stock is there for "just in case" the demand may spike and you dont have enough inventory to supply, so you have this safety stock to cover that spike while waiting for the lead time.  The variables you must consider are the demand (how much supply you need depends on what your demand is), holding cost (holding inventory cost), and lead time (how much time before the next shipment).  If you consider all these variables you can figure out the best amount of safety stock for your inventory just in case you have that spike.
